Title: Chiral bosonization as a Duality
Author: Mohammad R. Garousi
Comments: 9 pages, LaTex, no figures
Report-no: McGill/95-47
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D53 (1996) 2173-2177
\\
  We demonstrate that the technique of abelian bosonization through duality
transformations can be extended to gauging anomalous symmetries. The example of
a Dirac fermion theory is first illustrated. This idea is then also applied to
bosonize a chiral fermion by gauging its chiral phase symmetry.
